{
  "body": "## The problem\r\nThere is a shortcut for calling a sub with named arguments when the arguments and variables have the same names - `foo(:$x)` instead of `foo(x => $x)`.\r\nIt's hard to find it, though. It's only present [here](https://docs.perl6.org/type/Signature#index-entry-named_argument) as a cryptic `$ = :(:$a);`.\r\n## Suggestions\r\nThere should be an example - or a section - telling the reader that they can write `foo(:$x)` instead of `foo(x => $x)`.",
